hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: I'm training to be an engineer ironman mattress protector with celliant reviews Anthropologically speaking, tattoos are fascinating, and as self-expression goes it doesn't get much more tangible than puncturing a needle filled with indelible pigment into your body. I can understand what drives people to do it. Besides the immediate endorphine rush, I imagine that it's validating to commit yourself to such a palpable personal transformation. I see the appeal of exerting control over one’s body; I admire the permanence of them, and like the fact that they are emblems of signficant moments in our lives. I can see the attraction of attempting to mould your external being to fit your idea of ‘the real you’. Sometimes the sexiest thing about a tattoo is simply the fact that the owner doesn't care what others think of it. 'Good for you!' I think.
